e of the resulting cross-section curve (versus laser wavelength) at\nthreshold and up to an excitation energy of about 1 eV is in good agreement\nwith experimental cross sections. The equations for the methods are explicitly\nadapted to spherical symmetry (involving radial integrals and angular factors)\nand in this form permit a rapid computation for systems in intermediate\nconfinement.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 19 Feb 2022 12:56:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 27 Apr 2022 15:28:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-28"}
